{"video_id": "rGdn_0Yg94Q", "title": "Daily Evening Bhagavatam Discourse | HH Stoka Krishna Swami | SB 1.13.16 | 29-09-2022", "speaker": "HH Stoka Krishna Swami", "youtube_url": "https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=rGdn_0Yg94Q", "duration": 942, "segments": [{"start": 0.0, "end": 30.0, "text": " ओम ज्ञान तिमिरान दस्या ज्ञानां जिनिशलाकया चक्षिरुन मेरितम येना दस्मै श्री गुरवेनमहा नमाओ विश्णु पादाया कृष्ण प्रेष्ठाय भूतले श्रीमते भक्ति वेदांत स्वामिन नितिनामिने नमस्ते सारस्वते देवे गव्रवाणी गचारि"}, {"start": 30.0, "end": 60.0, "text": " सादेगो रबत ταश्राण हमारे कृष्णा हरें कृष्ण कृष्ण कृष्ण हरें हरें हरे राम हरे रामाराम अरे न by द वाया न संयर नमानाराईण स्कृति प्रक्रिया शेंष वन अरकाउन डे विधि द्या संतोथियों गुंधी"}, {"start": 60.0, "end": 75.0, "text": " युदिष्ठिरो लब्धराज्यो दृष्ट्वा पाउत्रं कुलंधरं ब्रात्रदेल लोकपालाभयर मुमुदे परयाश्रियाः"}, {"start": 75.0, "end": 78.0, "text": " So meaning of this verse is"}, {"start": 78.0, "end": 85.0, "text": " Having won his kingdom and observed the birth of one grandson competent to continue the noble tradition of his family,"}, {"start": 85.0, "end": 98.0, "text": " Maharaj Yudhishthira reigned peacefully and enjoyed uncommon opulence in cooperation with his younger brothers who were all expert administrators to the common people."}, {"start": 98.0, "end": 106.0, "text": " So this verse is describing what is Yudhishthira's position when Vidura is visiting Yudhishthira."}, {"start": 106.0, "end": 114.0, "text": " Vidura's purpose is not to enjoy any nice hospitality."}, {"start": 114.0, "end": 120.0, "text": " Rather, he has come to instruct Dhritharashtra,"}, {"start": 120.0, "end": 131.0, "text": " to rescue Dhritharashtra from his so-called comfortable living towards the end of his life."}, {"start": 131.0, "end": 136.0, "text": " Instead of preparing for putting the body through self-realization,"}, {"start": 136.0, "end": 142.0, "text": " Dhritharashtra is completely neglectful of his spiritual responsibility."}, {"start": 142.0, "end": 144.0, "text": " So Vidura has come to instruct Dhritharashtra,"}, {"start": 144.0, "end": 157.0, "text": " to save him from missing the opportunity for self-realization in his human form of life."}, {"start": 157.0, "end": 159.0, "text": " So what about Yudhishthira?"}, {"start": 159.0, "end": 163.0, "text": " So that is being explained by Prabhupada in this partho."}, {"start": 163.0, "end": 172.0, "text": " Yudhishthira was, the verse says, ruling very nicely, assisted by his younger brothers who were all expert administrators."}, {"start": 172.0, "end": 177.0, "text": " And he had a competent grandson because as soon as Parikeet was born,"}, {"start": 177.0, "end": 185.0, "text": " the learned astrologist told he is a competent successor for Yudhishthira."}, {"start": 185.0, "end": 189.0, "text": " When he grows up, he will have excellent qualities."}, {"start": 189.0, "end": 197.0, "text": " So Yudhishthira was very peacefully ruling, waiting for his grandson to grow up and take charge."}, {"start": 197.0, "end": 201.0, "text": " Till then Yudhishthira was accepting to rule the whole world."}, {"start": 202.0, "end": 207.0, "text": " Now Srila Prabhupada says something important about Yudhishthira."}, {"start": 207.0, "end": 217.0, "text": " That both Maharaj Yudhishthira and Arjuna were unhappy from the beginning of the battle of Kurukshetra."}, {"start": 217.0, "end": 219.0, "text": " Why were they unhappy?"}, {"start": 219.0, "end": 223.0, "text": " They were not very comfortable fighting against their own kinsmen,"}, {"start": 223.0, "end": 231.0, "text": " simply for the sake of getting their share of the kingdom to rule."}, {"start": 232.0, "end": 243.0, "text": " Duryodhana cleverly cheated the Pandavas and sent them away for exile, 13 years."}, {"start": 243.0, "end": 252.0, "text": " So even after the term of exile is over, Duryodhana refused to give back the share of the kingdom."}, {"start": 252.0, "end": 259.0, "text": " So then Kshatriya code of conduct is, if a Kshatriya challenges,"}, {"start": 259.0, "end": 262.0, "text": " then another Kshatriya cannot refuse the challenge."}, {"start": 262.0, "end": 268.0, "text": " So Yudhishthira could not refuse the challenge offered by Duryodhana."}, {"start": 268.0, "end": 273.0, "text": " So Yudhishthira had to engage in fighting the battle of Kurukshetra."}, {"start": 273.0, "end": 277.0, "text": " Because Duryodhana challenged."}, {"start": 277.0, "end": 283.0, "text": " So even Arjuna, even though he was very very powerful,"}, {"start": 283.0, "end": 289.0, "text": " even Yudhishthira was very powerful and strong and not afraid of fighting."}, {"start": 289.0, "end": 296.0, "text": " But he did not like to fight for the sake of gaining some kingdom."}, {"start": 296.0, "end": 300.0, "text": " Because by and heart he is a pure devotee."}, {"start": 300.0, "end": 303.0, "text": " Both Yudhishthira and Arjuna are pure devotees."}, {"start": 303.0, "end": 309.0, "text": " Therefore it is described by Prabhupada here that they were unhappy from the beginning."}, {"start": 309.0, "end": 312.0, "text": " Even though they were unwilling to kill their own men in the fight,"}, {"start": 312.0, "end": 316.0, "text": " it had to be done as a matter of duty."}, {"start": 316.0, "end": 317.0, "text": " Why?"}, {"start": 317.0, "end": 321.0, "text": " Because it was planned by the supreme will of Lord Krishna"}, {"start": 321.0, "end": 325.0, "text": " that somebody like Yudhishthira should rule the kingdom"}, {"start": 325.0, "end": 334.0, "text": " and not be corrupt, non-devotional Duryodhana."}, {"start": 334.0, "end": 342.0, "text": " Krishna wants the world to be ruled by his representative who is a devotee."}, {"start": 342.0, "end": 346.0, "text": " Such a devotee is the perfect person to rule."}, {"start": 347.0, "end": 355.0, "text": " Because people have to not only be taken care of in terms of their material necessities,"}, {"start": 355.0, "end": 363.0, "text": " but they should also be directed and protected"}, {"start": 363.0, "end": 369.0, "text": " for practicing spiritual life to make their human form of life successful"}, {"start": 369.0, "end": 375.0, "text": " by preparing themselves to go back to Godhead."}, {"start": 375.0, "end": 377.0, "text": " So that's why it is so important"}, {"start": 377.0, "end": 384.0, "text": " that the ruler not only be competent in terms of material qualifications"}, {"start": 384.0, "end": 386.0, "text": " to rule the kingdom,"}, {"start": 386.0, "end": 390.0, "text": " but also be spiritually competent to guide the citizens"}, {"start": 390.0, "end": 393.0, "text": " how they can side by side,"}, {"start": 393.0, "end": 395.0, "text": " apart from doing their material duties,"}, {"start": 395.0, "end": 397.0, "text": " also practice Krishna consciousness"}, {"start": 397.0, "end": 405.0, "text": " to actually prepare themselves for going back to Godhead."}, {"start": 405.0, "end": 406.0, "text": " So,"}, {"start": 406.0, "end": 409.0, "text": " because Krishna wanted Yudhishthira to go home"}, {"start": 409.0, "end": 414.0, "text": " and Duryodhana was not a devotee,"}, {"start": 414.0, "end": 418.0, "text": " so he was not giving any spiritual guidance to the people."}, {"start": 418.0, "end": 420.0, "text": " He himself was not a devotee."}, {"start": 420.0, "end": 424.0, "text": " So where would he give guidance to others to become devotees?"}, {"start": 424.0, "end": 428.0, "text": " So that is the reason Krishna wanted it,"}, {"start": 428.0, "end": 432.0, "text": " therefore as a duty they had to fight in the battle."}, {"start": 432.0, "end": 433.0, "text": " After the battle,"}, {"start": 433.0, "end": 436.0, "text": " Maharaj Yudhishthira was unhappy over such mass killings."}, {"start": 436.0, "end": 439.0, "text": " Huge massacre happened."}, {"start": 439.0, "end": 442.0, "text": " It was a world war."}, {"start": 442.0, "end": 446.0, "text": " So in that world war so many people died."}, {"start": 446.0, "end": 450.0, "text": " Practically there was none to continue the Kuru dynasty after them,"}, {"start": 450.0, "end": 452.0, "text": " the Pandavas."}, {"start": 452.0, "end": 455.0, "text": " Pandavas took charge of ruling."}, {"start": 455.0, "end": 460.0, "text": " But there were no descendants in the Kuru dynasty."}, {"start": 460.0, "end": 462.0, "text": " The only remaining hope"}, {"start": 462.0, "end": 464.0, "text": " was a child in the womb of"}, {"start": 464.0, "end": 466.0, "text": " Yudhishthira's daughter,"}, {"start": 466.0, "end": 468.0, "text": " Lavuktha Rao."}, {"start": 468.0, "end": 471.0, "text": " And that child in the womb"}, {"start": 471.0, "end": 474.0, "text": " was attacked by Ashwatthama."}, {"start": 474.0, "end": 477.0, "text": " Even the child in the womb was attacked by Ashwatthama."}, {"start": 477.0, "end": 482.0, "text": " The last surviving descendant of the entire Kuru dynasty"}, {"start": 482.0, "end": 484.0, "text": " was attacked by Ashwatthama."}, {"start": 484.0, "end": 486.0, "text": " But"}, {"start": 486.0, "end": 489.0, "text": " by the grace of the Supreme Lord Krishna"}, {"start": 489.0, "end": 491.0, "text": " the child was saved"}, {"start": 491.0, "end": 493.0, "text": " in the womb of the mother."}, {"start": 493.0, "end": 496.0, "text": " The child was saved by Krishna."}, {"start": 496.0, "end": 499.0, "text": " This has already been explained in an earlier chapter."}, {"start": 499.0, "end": 502.0, "text": " So after the settlement of all disturbing conditions"}, {"start": 502.0, "end": 506.0, "text": " and re-establishment of the peaceful order of the state"}, {"start": 506.0, "end": 510.0, "text": " and after seeing the surviving child Pariksha"}, {"start": 510.0, "end": 512.0, "text": " well satisfied"}, {"start": 512.0, "end": 515.0, "text": " Maharaj Yudhishthira felt some relief"}, {"start": 515.0, "end": 517.0, "text": " as a human being."}, {"start": 517.0, "end": 519.0, "text": " After the massacre"}, {"start": 519.0, "end": 521.0, "text": " Yudhishthira was very disturbed."}, {"start": 521.0, "end": 523.0, "text": " But he was instructed by"}, {"start": 523.0, "end": 524.0, "text": " Bhishma"}, {"start": 524.0, "end": 526.0, "text": " that he has to do his duty"}, {"start": 526.0, "end": 528.0, "text": " and not become afflicted"}, {"start": 528.0, "end": 531.0, "text": " by his sorrow over the"}, {"start": 531.0, "end": 534.0, "text": " big"}, {"start": 534.0, "end": 538.0, "text": " killing that has happened in the battle."}, {"start": 538.0, "end": 541.0, "text": " So he was pacified by Bhishma."}, {"start": 541.0, "end": 543.0, "text": " Yudhishthira was pacified by Bhishma."}, {"start": 543.0, "end": 546.0, "text": " And he was even more happy"}, {"start": 546.0, "end": 549.0, "text": " rather even more peaceful"}, {"start": 549.0, "end": 551.0, "text": " when this Pariksha was saved"}, {"start": 551.0, "end": 553.0, "text": " and Pariksha took birth"}, {"start": 553.0, "end": 556.0, "text": " as a competent descendant"}, {"start": 556.0, "end": 558.0, "text": " to ascend the throne after"}, {"start": 558.0, "end": 560.0, "text": " Yudhishthira Maharaj."}, {"start": 560.0, "end": 562.0, "text": " So things were settled"}, {"start": 562.0, "end": 565.0, "text": " and he felt some relief as a human being."}, {"start": 565.0, "end": 566.0, "text": " Although"}, {"start": 566.0, "end": 568.0, "text": " he had very little"}, {"start": 568.0, "end": 571.0, "text": " attraction for material happiness"}, {"start": 571.0, "end": 575.0, "text": " which is always illusory and temporary."}, {"start": 575.0, "end": 578.0, "text": " See Prabhupada is mentioning a very important point"}, {"start": 578.0, "end": 580.0, "text": " that material happiness"}, {"start": 580.0, "end": 582.0, "text": " which can be had"}, {"start": 582.0, "end": 585.0, "text": " by having a nice kingdom"}, {"start": 585.0, "end": 587.0, "text": " growing peacefully"}, {"start": 587.0, "end": 589.0, "text": " having a competent successor"}, {"start": 589.0, "end": 591.0, "text": " and having very able administrators"}, {"start": 591.0, "end": 593.0, "text": " as younger brothers"}, {"start": 593.0, "end": 595.0, "text": " younger brothers as administrators."}, {"start": 595.0, "end": 597.0, "text": " In spite of all this"}, {"start": 597.0, "end": 599.0, "text": " Yudhishthira as a pure devotee"}, {"start": 599.0, "end": 603.0, "text": " had no attraction for material happiness."}, {"start": 603.0, "end": 604.0, "text": " Why?"}, {"start": 604.0, "end": 606.0, "text": " Because as Prabhupada says here"}, {"start": 606.0, "end": 609.0, "text": " material happiness is always illusory"}, {"start": 609.0, "end": 611.0, "text": " and temporary."}, {"start": 611.0, "end": 614.0, "text": " Two characters only."}, {"start": 614.0, "end": 616.0, "text": " Illusory because"}, {"start": 616.0, "end": 618.0, "text": " material happiness"}, {"start": 618.0, "end": 622.0, "text": " is the happiness due to sense contact."}, {"start": 622.0, "end": 624.0, "text": " And what is the description of"}, {"start": 624.0, "end": 626.0, "text": " material happiness due to sense contact?"}, {"start": 626.0, "end": 628.0, "text": " In the Bhagavad Gita Krishna says"}, {"start": 628.0, "end": 629.0, "text": " in the fifth chapter"}, {"start": 629.0, "end": 632.0, "text": " yehi samsparsha ja bhoga"}, {"start": 632.0, "end": 634.0, "text": " dukha yonaya evade"}, {"start": 634.0, "end": 636.0, "text": " aadyantamant kaunteya"}, {"start": 636.0, "end": 638.0, "text": " na teshu ramate buddhah"}, {"start": 638.0, "end": 640.0, "text": " Intelligent people"}, {"start": 640.0, "end": 643.0, "text": " who are totally enlightened"}, {"start": 643.0, "end": 645.0, "text": " do not take pleasure"}, {"start": 645.0, "end": 650.0, "text": " in happiness arising from sense contact"}, {"start": 650.0, "end": 653.0, "text": " because they know"}, {"start": 653.0, "end": 656.0, "text": " all such happiness is"}, {"start": 656.0, "end": 659.0, "text": " simply a temporary sensation"}, {"start": 659.0, "end": 662.0, "text": " due to the sense contact"}, {"start": 662.0, "end": 664.0, "text": " and it is always a source of misery"}, {"start": 664.0, "end": 666.0, "text": " in the material world."}, {"start": 666.0, "end": 668.0, "text": " So what we think"}, {"start": 668.0, "end": 672.0, "text": " as a source of happiness"}, {"start": 672.0, "end": 679.0, "text": " is actually a disguised source of misery"}, {"start": 679.0, "end": 681.0, "text": " in the future."}, {"start": 681.0, "end": 684.0, "text": " All material happiness is like this."}, {"start": 684.0, "end": 688.0, "text": " It is promising"}, {"start": 688.0, "end": 692.0, "text": " to give us great amount of happiness"}, {"start": 692.0, "end": 695.0, "text": " but that is just a false promise."}, {"start": 696.0, "end": 698.0, "text": " It is due to illusion."}, {"start": 698.0, "end": 701.0, "text": " Due to illusion we consider"}, {"start": 701.0, "end": 703.0, "text": " some type of sense contact"}, {"start": 703.0, "end": 705.0, "text": " as favourable"}, {"start": 705.0, "end": 707.0, "text": " and another type of sense contact"}, {"start": 707.0, "end": 709.0, "text": " as unfavourable."}, {"start": 709.0, "end": 711.0, "text": " So when the sense contact is favourable"}, {"start": 711.0, "end": 714.0, "text": " we think it is happiness."}, {"start": 714.0, "end": 716.0, "text": " And when the same sense contact"}, {"start": 716.0, "end": 718.0, "text": " is unfavourable"}, {"start": 718.0, "end": 721.0, "text": " we think it is distress."}, {"start": 721.0, "end": 723.0, "text": " Prabhupada gives a simple example"}, {"start": 723.0, "end": 725.0, "text": " to help us understand."}, {"start": 725.0, "end": 727.0, "text": " It is like cold water."}, {"start": 727.0, "end": 729.0, "text": " In winter"}, {"start": 729.0, "end": 730.0, "text": " in the severe cold"}, {"start": 730.0, "end": 733.0, "text": " cold water is very unpleasant"}, {"start": 733.0, "end": 739.0, "text": " very harsh for the sense of touch."}, {"start": 739.0, "end": 740.0, "text": " The same cold water"}, {"start": 740.0, "end": 742.0, "text": " at the same temperature"}, {"start": 742.0, "end": 744.0, "text": " in summer"}, {"start": 744.0, "end": 746.0, "text": " it is very very pleasing"}, {"start": 746.0, "end": 748.0, "text": " for the sense of touch."}, {"start": 748.0, "end": 750.0, "text": " In fact we like to take"}, {"start": 750.0, "end": 752.0, "text": " a cold water bath in summer"}, {"start": 752.0, "end": 754.0, "text": " and it is very hot"}, {"start": 754.0, "end": 755.0, "text": " outside."}, {"start": 755.0, "end": 758.0, "text": " So it is just the"}, {"start": 758.0, "end": 761.0, "text": " contact which is"}, {"start": 761.0, "end": 763.0, "text": " due to some particular"}, {"start": 763.0, "end": 765.0, "text": " situation or condition"}, {"start": 765.0, "end": 767.0, "text": " it is either interpreted as"}, {"start": 767.0, "end": 769.0, "text": " happiness or distress based on"}, {"start": 769.0, "end": 770.0, "text": " whether it is favourable contact"}, {"start": 770.0, "end": 772.0, "text": " or unfavourable contact."}, {"start": 772.0, "end": 774.0, "text": " This is the nature of"}, {"start": 774.0, "end": 777.0, "text": " all kinds of sense contact."}, {"start": 777.0, "end": 780.0, "text": " We have five primary senses"}, {"start": 780.0, "end": 781.0, "text": " external senses"}, {"start": 781.0, "end": 783.0, "text": " the eyes, ears, nose, tongue"}, {"start": 783.0, "end": 785.0, "text": " sense of touch, skin"}, {"start": 785.0, "end": 788.0, "text": " and we have one sense within the mind."}, {"start": 788.0, "end": 790.0, "text": " Now including the mind"}, {"start": 790.0, "end": 792.0, "text": " with these six senses"}, {"start": 792.0, "end": 794.0, "text": " we are trying to enjoy happiness"}, {"start": 794.0, "end": 796.0, "text": " material happiness of this world."}, {"start": 796.0, "end": 799.0, "text": " But our only avenue for"}, {"start": 799.0, "end": 801.0, "text": " material happiness through these senses"}, {"start": 801.0, "end": 803.0, "text": " is sense contact."}, {"start": 803.0, "end": 805.0, "text": " And that sense contact"}, {"start": 805.0, "end": 807.0, "text": " simply"}, {"start": 807.0, "end": 809.0, "text": " is"}, {"start": 809.0, "end": 811.0, "text": " a"}, {"start": 811.0, "end": 813.0, "text": " concoction in our mind"}, {"start": 813.0, "end": 815.0, "text": " and we are trying to enjoy"}, {"start": 815.0, "end": 817.0, "text": " something that is not so nice"}, {"start": 817.0, "end": 819.0, "text": " or something that is painful"}, {"start": 819.0, "end": 821.0, "text": " or something that is pleasurable."}, {"start": 823.0, "end": 825.0, "text": " Just like another example"}, {"start": 825.0, "end": 827.0, "text": " if you are given"}, {"start": 827.0, "end": 829.0, "text": " some edible"}, {"start": 829.0, "end": 831.0, "text": " which you like to eat"}, {"start": 833.0, "end": 834.0, "text": " you will think"}, {"start": 834.0, "end": 835.0, "text": " oh it is so nice"}, {"start": 835.0, "end": 837.0, "text": " I am having this for eating"}, {"start": 837.0, "end": 839.0, "text": " because you like the taste"}, {"start": 839.0, "end": 841.0, "text": " the contact of that"}, {"start": 841.0, "end": 842.0, "text": " edible"}, {"start": 842.0, "end": 844.0, "text": " with your sense of taste"}, {"start": 844.0, "end": 846.0, "text": " oh so nice."}, {"start": 846.0, "end": 848.0, "text": " The same thing"}, {"start": 848.0, "end": 849.0, "text": " for somebody else"}, {"start": 849.0, "end": 851.0, "text": " who does not like it."}, {"start": 851.0, "end": 854.0, "text": " They when they look at it"}, {"start": 854.0, "end": 855.0, "text": " oh I don't like it"}, {"start": 855.0, "end": 857.0, "text": " I don't want it."}, {"start": 857.0, "end": 860.0, "text": " So even if it is edible"}, {"start": 860.0, "end": 862.0, "text": " even if it is to the liking of somebody"}, {"start": 862.0, "end": 864.0, "text": " some other person"}, {"start": 864.0, "end": 866.0, "text": " for me it is not likeable"}, {"start": 866.0, "end": 868.0, "text": " so I don't consider it as"}, {"start": 868.0, "end": 870.0, "text": " a pleasurable experience"}, {"start": 870.0, "end": 871.0, "text": " to eat such an edible."}, {"start": 871.0, "end": 877.0, "text": " So the same thing"}, {"start": 877.0, "end": 879.0, "text": " according to our"}, {"start": 879.0, "end": 881.0, "text": " concoction"}, {"start": 881.0, "end": 883.0, "text": " of likes and dislikes"}, {"start": 889.0, "end": 891.0, "text": " we are born into this material world"}, {"start": 891.0, "end": 893.0, "text": " with certain set of likes and dislikes"}, {"start": 893.0, "end": 895.0, "text": " material likes and material dislikes"}, {"start": 895.0, "end": 897.0, "text": " and exactly according to these"}, {"start": 897.0, "end": 899.0, "text": " likes and dislikes"}, {"start": 899.0, "end": 901.0, "text": " we consider something"}, {"start": 901.0, "end": 902.0, "text": " as pleasurable"}, {"start": 902.0, "end": 904.0, "text": " and something as not pleasurable."}, {"start": 907.0, "end": 910.0, "text": " So this is the basis of all"}, {"start": 910.0, "end": 913.0, "text": " material happiness and distress."}, {"start": 914.0, "end": 916.0, "text": " So neither happiness"}, {"start": 916.0, "end": 917.0, "text": " nor distress"}, {"start": 917.0, "end": 919.0, "text": " is actually"}, {"start": 919.0, "end": 922.0, "text": " the reality."}, {"start": 922.0, "end": 923.0, "text": " Reality is"}, {"start": 923.0, "end": 925.0, "text": " it is illusion."}, {"start": 925.0, "end": 926.0, "text": " It is illusion."}, {"start": 926.0, "end": 928.0, "text": " But we"}, {"start": 928.0, "end": 930.0, "text": " in ignorance"}, {"start": 930.0, "end": 932.0, "text": " we seek after material happiness"}, {"start": 932.0, "end": 934.0, "text": " and try to avoid material distress."}, {"start": 934.0, "end": 935.0, "text": " And we are always"}, {"start": 935.0, "end": 936.0, "text": " in this way"}, {"start": 936.0, "end": 937.0, "text": " under illusion."}, {"start": 937.0, "end": 939.0, "text": " So that is being explained."}, {"start": 939.0, "end": 940.0, "text": " I will stop here."}, {"start": 940.0, "end": 941.0, "text": " Thank you very much."}, {"start": 941.0, "end": 942.0, "text": " Hare Krishna."}]}